19:
What's with Helga? Not like her to be 
this quiet.
Heeeey, you listenin'?
22:
I am trying to, yes, now hush. Don't 
you hear something?
36:
*sniffle* ...Huh? A big doggie? And 
a kitty?
38:
Yes, sweetie. Now what are you doing 
here all on your lonesome?
41:
Uwaaaah! Dad—*hic*—Daddyyyy! 
Where'sh Daddy!? I want my daddy!
44:
Damn it, why'd you put ME in charge of 
watchin' the kid?!
47:
YOU take him Helga! You're good with 
kids, right?
51:
No! I-I don't know how to stop him 
crying either, but... Oh, all right, I'll try!
59:
Arf! Arf arf! Look at the big funny 
doggie!
63:
There, there, that's better. Doggie will 
help get you home to your daddy.
69:
Emil! What a cool name, for a very 
brave boy! Now then, Emil sweetie, can 
you tell me why you're here in the 
Kaleidoscope?
71:
I'm looking for my daddy. He... he went 
to work in the Kaleidoscope, but... 
*sniffle* He didn't come home.
73:
He, he said he'd be home by dinner, 
but he never came... S-so I came to 
find him!
75:
Alone? What you did is very 
dangerous. It's a miracle you're 
unharmed.
79:
I never really thought much of it, but 
Palpebra DOES have a lot of 
orphanages...
80:
Hey, Emil. Can you tell me how long it's 
been since your daddy disappeared?
83:
A-about two days? The day before 
yesterday.
87:
I might still be able to track him. Come 
here, sweetie, let doggie give you 
a good sniff.
89:
I can't make any promises, but I'll see 
what I can do.
94:
I'll go with you.
Alk, Light, get that kid outta here.
100:
Alk and I will retrace the path we 
cleared back to the entrance. Now, go! 
I trust your noses, and your unyielding 
strength!
104:
I just said I can't make any promises! 
The scent is very faint.
109:
Then quit your damn bellyachin' and 
get your ass in gear! Let's go! The 
trail's not getting any stronger 
standing around here, is it?
113:
Quit my damn bellyaching, eh? Hmph, 
you're absolutely right, but you had 
better watch your language when 
addressing a lady.
117: I damn sure as hell won't.
119:
Heh. C'mon, we won't know unless we 
try.
121:
We "damn sure as hell won't," will we? 
Come—follow me!
127:
Emil! Oh, Emil, Daddy's so sorry! I'm so 
glad you're safe.
128:
Yup! There was a big talking doggie 
and a stripey kitty and they saved me! 
...Huh? Where are they?
134:
Welcome back, Helga. Alk explained 
the situation. It's a good thing you 
were around.
138:
A good thing I was around? ...Thank 
you, Stella.
